   @{fg fill}@{bg shine} Windows NT @{fg text}@{bg back}- Already built in....

    When using Windows NT, go into the control panel/networks. Under
    the services tab add the option for Microsoft TCP/IP printing.
    Ensure this service runs all the time.

    Once this is done, you will have to share your printer as normal. ie
    right click on the printer and select sharing. You are asked to give
    the printer a share name, this share name becomes the netpar printer
    name when printing from the network.

   @{fg shine}@{bg fill} Information on NT supplied by Francois Prowse @{fg text}@{bg back}





